{
  "texts": [
    "To address these challenges, this review paper seeks to explores the application of AI in automating the SR process and to provide a comprehensive overview of the current AI techniques proposed.",
    "Thus, this paper aims to equip researchers with a foundational understanding of the basic concepts, primary methodologies, and advancements in SR AI automation.",
    "To the best of knowledge, there exists only one study by Jaspers et al. (2018) that provides a detailed overview of the ML approach employed in SR.",
    "However, the study focuses on only one branch of AI and only partially covers the NLP and DL aspects of the AI used for SR automation.",
    "Additionally, the review focused on ML techniques used for only SRs within the domain of the Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA)."
  ]
}